The national government yesterday gave in to public pressure and formed a multi-agency committee to spearhead talks on the exit package for commissioners of the electoral agency.The committee brings together representatives from the Treasury, the Office of the Attorney General, Ministry of Interior and Coordination of National Government, Ministry of Public Service and the Salaries and Remuneration Commission and is expected to commence negotiations with the nine Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commissioners set to vacate office. The inter-agency committee will lead negotiations with the IEBC commissioners to facilitate their orderly and dignified exit and ensure a seamless transition within the commission, government spokesman Erick Kiraithe said yesterday.